[div class=p 
	"Yes, I once spent 4 hours and ended up in the same place. So much for having to redo sections.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Also, three times I ran into a flawed savestate desync. The problem seems to occur if you save after the movie ended and loaded it later. I would have been more raged if I didn't know how to hex-edit.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=http://i19.photobucket.com/albums/b185/jhchan8/mm8/snap_074.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=AboutTheGame 
	" About the game
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	[img class=embedright mw-100 src=http://i19.photobucket.com/albums/b185/jhchan8/mm8/snap_004.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"One of Capcom's Mega Man games. Fun to TAS, not so fun to play.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Graphics and sound effects are very detailed. On the other hand, voice acting isn't so good. Then again, could voice acting ever be good? The best bosses tear you apart silently.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Regarding the plot, 
	[a href=http://speeddemosarchive.com/MegaMan8.html rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Cremator has it right
	]a
	":
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[em 
		"In this part of the Mega Man saga, Mega Man goes on a rampage to hurt and destroy innocent Robot Masters that talk funny; he was going to settle with four at first, but Frost Man was just too much. That's all you need to know about the plot.
	]em
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Weapons 
	" Weapons
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Due to how the game works, you have a lot of freedom in using weapons:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" You can use both a special weapon and Mega Buster at the same time.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" You can charge up right away after releasing a charged shot, rather than waiting for it to disappear.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" You can charge up during most scenes while waiting.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"This of course is common to Mega Man PSX games. But wait, there's more! In Mega Man 8, that is:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" You can switch special weapons 
		[b 
			"any time
		]b
		", and fire any special weapons 
		[b 
			"any time
		]b
		". (Subject to firing limits on each individual weapon, as well as what you're firing at the moment).
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" You can arm yourself with Mega Buster only, and autofire 60Hz by alternating the two fire keys. (Subject to three-shot limit, of course).
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=http://i19.photobucket.com/albums/b185/jhchan8/mm8/snap_044.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Let's go over the weapons, shall we?
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" Mega Buster: Charge it up, fire. POWERSHOT. Highly effective, you'd think Mega Man was taking photos.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Mega Ball: More a tool than a weapon. This is the reason Mega Man can fly up very quickly. Even faster if near a wall, as the shots are closer to you.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Tornado Hold: Can be used to ascend in place of the Mega Ball. Using both allows you to go up quickly. However, Tornado Hold may interfere with your path.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Thunder Claw: Not used much as it prevents Mega Man from acting, except when he's in air. But it does good damage.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Flash Bomb: Does good damage, but should be deployed far from the target. Also used on bosses to delay hits (to charge up).
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Ice Wave: Same as Flash Bomb, except for the delayed hits thing.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Water Balloon: Despite the name, it is very powerful and kills non-bosses easily. No shot limit, can be autofired at 30Hz.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Flame Sword: Similar to Thunder Claw, prevents Mega Man from acting. Can be used to hit some blocks from above.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Homing Sniper: Attacks the nearest (targetable) enemy. Very useful, as it can hit above and below, whereas other weapons can't.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Astro Crush: Only used on bosses, as it stops Mega Man. Even then, not so useful.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h4 id=Upgrades 
	" Upgrades
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	[img class=embedright mw-100 src=http://i19.photobucket.com/albums/b185/jhchan8/mm8/snap_036.png 
	]img
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"I get only the Hyper Slider, which increases sliding speed. Other items save less, and take more time (you have to collect the large bolts).
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=Route 
	" Route
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Grenade -> Frost -> Tengu -> Clown -> Astro -> Aqua -> Sword -> Search
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Grenade Man is first due to Rush Bike, which saves a lot of time in Clown Man's stage. Astro is first after Duo because his weakness does only 3 (rather than 4 like others), and Flash Bomb (the best one due to delayed hits) does 2 damage.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=LuckManipulation 
	" Luck Manipulation
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"I needed a lot of it, no doubt.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Things that change RNG: Time delay, POWERSHOT, Flash Bomb, Ice Wave, Thunder Claw, Homing Sniper, Astro Crush.
	$LF
]div
